<p class="hero">
<strong>RawEverything</strong> serves raw files directly from GitHub, Dropbox, Bitbucket, FilesAnywhere, and Launchpad with the <strong>Content-Type</strong> rewritten to the correct type for the file.
</p>

<div class="pure-g-r url-helper">
    <div class="pure-u-1">
        <p id="url-form">
            <label for="url" class="offscreen">GitHub file, Github gist, Dropbox, Bitbucket, FilesAnywhere, or Launchpad URL:</label>
            <input id="url" class="url" type="url" placeholder="Paste a file URL here." autofocus>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="column pure-u-1-2">
        <h2>Use this URL for dev/testing</h2>

        <p>
        <input id="url-dev" class="url" placeholder="https://{{config.devDomain}}/NewFilePath" readonly>
        </p>

        <ul>
        <li><p>For sharing <strong>low-traffic, temporary examples or demos</strong> with small numbers of people.
        <li><p>Excessive traffic may lead to throttling and blacklisting.
        <li><p>New changes you push to your file host will be reflected within minutes.
        <li><p>If excessive traffic continues after throttling and blacklisting, RewriteEverything may display an error message to users on your site to try to get your attention.
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="column pure-u-1-2">
        <h2>Use this URL in production</h2>

        <p>
        <input id="url-prod" class="url" placeholder="https://{{config.cdnDomain}}/NewFilePath" readonly>
        </p>

        <ul>
         <li><p>For use on production websites with <strong>any amount of traffic</strong>. Files are served via <a href="http://www.maxcdn.com/">MaxCDN</a>'s super fast global CDN.
        <li><p>No traffic limits or throttling.
        <li><p>For source code repositories it's best to use a specific tag or commit hash in the URL (not a branch). Files are cached permanently after the first request.
        <li><p>The catch: this is a free service, so there are <a href="/faq#no-uptime-guarantee">no uptime or support guarantees</a>.
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
var cdnDomain = '{{config.cdnDomain}}';
var devDomain = '{{config.devDomain}}';
</script>
<script src="{{{assetUrl "/js/url-formatter.js"}}}"></script>
